The paper deals with the use of multiple-input-multiple-output (MIMO) technology in backscatter communication (BSC) for low power networking. This involves channel estimation and throughput fairness, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a low-complexity algorithm, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of MIMO technology in BSC also involves system optimization (cs.SY) and signal processing (cs.MM).
